  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Self-Employment Creation for Rural Youth to Build Peaceful Environment and Enhance Social Cohesion in Mali</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the context of transition, following the August 2020 coup in Mali and the upcoming elections, armed groups continue to mobilize more youth lacking economic opportunities in their communities, especially in rural areas. The project is an initiative targeting young male and female populations to reverse this trend in order to contribute to the prevention of the spread of the crisis marked by violent extremism in the south of the country. The project aims at creating decent employment opportunities for rural youth, including returnees, in the agricultural and livestock sectors, in order to strengthen social cohesion and significantly contribute to the consolidation of peace efforts in Mali by improving the prospects of young people with respect to their future and their role in the dynamics of peace while integrating aspects of adaptation to climate change and rural poverty reduction.</narrative>
  </description>
